        }
      }, "Probably the most important contact was the efforts made at evangelization of the Indians.  About the same time the Champlain was making his explorations up the Ottawa, the Recollet friars erected a mission at Huronia for the Huron Indians south of Georgian Bay.  This passed to the Jesuits in 1626."), /*#__PURE__*/React.createElement("p", {
