        }
      }, "Plans were made to go to Lake Sparrow on August 7, 1882, by way of the Pittsburgh & Lake Erie Railroad.  The financial arrangements for this first trip of the Club were much more modest than those of the Fiftieth.  Before the date of starting each member paid to the Treasurer $11.00 for railroad fare and $9.00 to cover cost of provisions, table and kitchen outfit, wages of the cook, and hire of five skiffs."), /*#__PURE__*/React.createElement("p", {
