      }, "A uniform camp dress was informally adopted, prominent in which were a heavy blue flannel shirt and folding tan linen Lone Fisherman hat at that time so popular for outing wear.  In addition to these purchased items, the uniform was completed from home wardrobes with a most astonishing assortment of old trousers.  These well served the purpose, but the less written of them here the better.  Let them be remembered tenderly for their service, not their beauty."), /*#__PURE__*/React.createElement("p", {
