      }, "The Club left old Lake Erie station at 10:40 o\u2019clock on the morning of Monday, August 7, 1882.  The trip was made in a combination car, the Club members occupying the passenger section and their baggage filling the other.  The journey was marked by a lengthening series of bumpy transfers of the special car from one train to another, these being made at Youngstown, Ashtabula, Buffalo, Suspension Bridge and Hamilton."), /*#__PURE__*/React.createElement("p", {
