        }
      }, "At Youngstown a telegram was sent to Toronto asking the Northern and Northwestern Railway Company to charter to the Club a special engine to haul the car at night without loss of time from Hamilton to Severn Bridge.  The engine was ready at Hamilton and the special night trip was begun.  In the morning as they neared their destination, the awaking members of the party discovered that the railroad company, in a fit of great generosity, had thrown in with the engine a long freight train for good measure, and were hauling it with the Club\u2019s chartered engine, with the Club car rattling along jauntily at the tail end.  The Club members were deeply impressed by this gracious act."), /*#__PURE__*/React.createElement("p", {
