        }
      }, "Later the \u201CJohn Lee\u201D was chartered for the purpose, and after it burned, arrangements were made with the Northern Navigation Company to have the steamer \u201CWaubic\u201D branch off its regular run to Parry Sound to Jubilee Island and take us in to our dock.  The \u201CWaubic\u201D made the run between Penetang and Parry Sound under contract with the Grand Trunk railroad, but the service never paid expenses, and as soon as the contract expired the Northern Navigation Company refused to renew it."), /*#__PURE__*/React.createElement("p", {
        __self: this,
