        }
      }, "There has always been an element that wanted more diversion than merely fishing.  When the present property was purchased, 1901, a tennis court was built, and surfaced with clay brought from Penetang, and tennis is still one of the outstanding sports of camp life.  A croquet ground was also laid out, and for years it was the chief land sport.  But the site has been smoothed up for a soft ball field now, and last year witnessed the first contest with an outside team in which we came in second best.  A team of Indians from Christian Island did things to our team that very greatly surprised them."), /*#__PURE__*/React.createElement("p", {
